      "content": "Based on the latest intelligence, there are several highly credible, albeit subtle, indicators that suggest heightened tensions, but nothing that points to an immediate military escalation. We are seeing increased logistical movements along the border, which is standard procedure for pre-summit security reviews, but the rhetoric from key military figures is more pointed than usual. I recommend framing the assessment as \"elevated operational readiness\" rather than \"imminent threat\" for the Ambassador's briefing.",
